id: pm-1jtl
title: "GH-250: pm close checks item existence before the close-reason gate"
description: "pm close checks governance.require_close_reason before verifying the target item exists, so a typo'd id with no reason reports 'Close reason text is required' instead of 'Item not found'. Validate existence before the close-reason gate in runClose (and keep close-many consistent)."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[3]: close,governance,ux
created_at: "2026-06-16T14:46:43.757Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-16T15:57:32.597Z"
author: claude-code-agent
parent: pm-mpbb
resolution: Locate item via buildItemNotFoundError before normalizeCloseReason.
expected_result: "Missing id with no reason reports not-found, not close-reason-required"
actual_result: Implemented in close.ts; new GH-250 close test green.
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-16T15:26:00.896Z",claude-code-agent,"GH-250 fix: runClose now locates the target item (buildItemNotFoundError) BEFORE normalizeCloseReason, so a typo'd id with no reason reports 'Item not found' instead of the misleading 'Close reason text is required'. close-many needs no change (ids come from a matched list, never user-typed). File: cli/commands/close.ts."
close_reason: "pm close validates item existence before the close-reason gate, so typo'd ids report 'Item not found' immediately."
